<p><italic>Life of Imitation – Paintings</italic> are based on a series of cinema billboards, originally produced for the Singapore Pavilion at the 53rd Venice Biennale 2009. Playing with language, performance and identity, Wong revisited Singapore’s ‘Golden Age’ of cinema of the 50s and 60s, to create three multi-screen installations, including <italic>Life of Imitation</italic>, alongside collaborative artworks with Singapore’s last cinema billboard painter. Referencing a scene from Douglas Sirk’s Hollywood melodrama <italic>Imitation of Life</italic> (1959), this series of images was repainted in December 2011.</p>
<p>All images courtesy of the artist.</p>
